.TH "rsu_send_msg" 9 "rsu_send_msg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rsu_send_msg \- send a message to Intel service layer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" rsu_send_msg
.BI "(struct stratix10_rsu_priv *priv "  ","
.BI "enum stratix10_svc_command_code command "  ","
.BI "unsigned long arg "  ","
.BI "rsu_callback callback "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "priv" 12
pointer to rsu private data
.IP "command" 12
RSU status or update command
.IP "arg" 12
the request argument, the bitstream address or notify status
.IP "callback" 12
function pointer for the callback (status or update)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Start an Intel service layer transaction to perform the SMC call that
is necessary to get RSU boot log or set the address of bitstream to
boot after reboot.

Returns 0 on success or -ETIMEDOUT on error.
